Function CanJump(nums):
    If nums is empty:
        Return False
    
    maxReach = 0
    
    For each index i from 0 to len(nums) - 1:
        If i is greater than maxReach:
            Return False (can't reach this position)
        
        maxReach = max(maxReach, i + nums[i])  // Update maxReach with the furthest we can jump from here
        
        If maxReach is greater than or equal to last index:
            Return True (can reach last index)
    
    Return False (if loop completes and last index isn't reachable)



